ev4score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Garner |first1=George |title=ALBUM REVIEW: BRITISH LION \u2013 THE BURNING |url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Kerrang! |accessdate=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5      = ''Metal Temple''\n| rev5score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nowels |first1=Dave |title=British Lion \u2013 The Burning |url=http://www.metal-temple.com/site/catalogues/entry/reviews/cd_3/b_2/british-lion-the.htm |website=Metal-Temple.com |accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6      = ''Distorted Sound''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|8|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Leaver |first1=Elliot |title=ALBUM REVIEW: The Burning \u2013 British Lion |url=https://distortedsoundmag.com/album-review-the-burning-british-lion/ |website=Distorted Sound Magazine |accessdate=January 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev7      = ''Planet Mosh''\n| rev7score = {{Rating|8|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Colson |first1=Stephen |title=The Burning \u2013 British Lion |url=https://planetmosh.com/the-burning-british-lion/ |website=PlanetMosh |accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev8      = ''Medium''\n| rev8score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Maturo |first1=Dave |title=Album Review \u2014 British Lion |url=https://medium.com/@davematuro/album-review-british-lion-5604a0a929c3 |website=Medium |accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Burning''''' is the second album by [[Iron Maiden]]'s bass guitarist [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] project called [[British Lion (band)|British Lion]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Childers |first1=Chad |title=British Lion Reveal \u2018The Burning\u2019 Album Details + 2020 U.S. Tour  Read More: British Lion Reveal 'The Burning' Album Details + 2020 U.S. Tour |url=https://loudwire.com/british-lion-the-burning-album-2020-u-s-tour/?utm_source=tsmclip&utm_medium=referral |website=Loudwire |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ryan |first1=Tim |title=Local CD pick: 'The Burning,\" British Lion |url=https://eu.sctimes.com/story/entertainment/2020/01/22/local-cd-pick-the-burning-british-lion/4523344002/ |website=sctimes.com |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Monkhouse |first1=Paul |title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning |url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/ |website=Metal Planet Music |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Popoff |first1=Martin |title=BRITISH LION \u2013 \u201cIT\u2019S EMOTIONAL AND IT\u2019S POWERFUL AND IT\u2019S REAL\u201d |url=http://bravewords.com/features/british-lion-its-emotional-and-its-powerful-and-its-real |website=BraveWords |accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Kevin |title=Steve Harris and British Lion Release \u201cThe Burning\u201d |url=https://www.notreble.com/buzz/2020/01/22/steve-harris-and-british-lion-release-the-burning/ |website=No Treble |accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref> It was released January 17, 2020, and was produced by Harris itself. It was the first album under only moniker [[British Lion (Band)|British Lion]], transforming the project from solo to band.\n\nThe album was preceded by the singles \"Spit Fire\" on October 26, 2018, \"Lightning\" on October 31, 2019, and the title track \"The Burning\" on December 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=IRON MAIDEN Bassist's BRITISH LION: Watch Music Video For 'The Burning' Title Track |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/iron-maiden-bassists-british-lion-watch-music-video-for-the-burning-title-track/ |website=Blabbermouth.net |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kielty |first1=Martin |title=Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019  Read More: Listen to Steve Harris\u2019 New British Lion Song \u2018The Burning\u2019 |url=https://ultimateclassicrock.com/british-lion-the-burning/ |website=ultimateclassicrock.com |accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Colothan |first1=Scott |title=Exclusive: British Lion premiere 'The Burning' video |url=https://planetradio.co.uk/planet-rock/news/rock-news/british-lion-the-burning-video/|website=planetradio.co.uk |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Graff |first1=Gary |title=Steve Harris Shares Title Track to British Lion's 'The Burning': Premiere |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8545910/british-lion-the-burning-steve-harris |website=Billboard |accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the release of ''The Burning'', critics published reviews on their thoughts of the album. Metal Planet Music voiced that \"the first thing that strikes you is the music, great hard rock with melody and class, but it\u2019s the heart and emotion that will stay with you long after the last note rings out. Coming eight years after their debut, \u2018''The Burning''\u2019 is the second album by British Lion and the [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] led quintet have made a record that is at once modern, nostalgic and timeless\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalplanetmusic.com/2020/01/gig-review-british-lion-the-burning/|title=Album Review : British Lion \u2013 \u2018The Burning|last=Authoradmin|date=2020-01-22|website=Metal Planet Music|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n[[Kerrang!]] mainly spoke upon the vocals of the album stating that \"the band's debut was rather a baptism of fire for singer Richard Taylor, who had to weather some predictable yet redundant criticisms comparing him to [[Bruce Dickinson]] from Steve\u2019s \u201cother\u201d band. He sings like he has a point to prove throughout ''The Burning''. A telling sign of the frontman's burgeoning confidence comes on \"Elysium\" \u2013 a song that boasts a killer chorus but an even better final passage, as he belts out a series of absolutely massive sustained notes over a swelling choral section. Equally impressive is his ability to extract emotion from a song. Whether he's communing with lost souls on \"Lightning\" or offering a consolatory ear on closer \"Native Son\", he often brings a moving sense of fragility to the fore. Clearly, this particular lion has more at its disposal than claws alone\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-british-lion-the-burning/|title=Album Review: British Lion \u2013 The Burning|website=Kerrang!|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nMetal Temple deemed the album a 9/10 saying \u201c''The Burning''\u201d is just what a sophomore album should be. A continuation, with enthusiasm, growth and development. [[Steve Harris (musician)|Harris]] is his usual subdued bass thumping brilliance. Hawkins and Leslie's dual guitar attack is on point, Dawson's drums precise and well deftly executed. Taylor's vocals add a final layer of confidence to the formula that seals the deal. British Lion's \"''The Burning''\" is refreshing in its telling of the story, and hints of even better tales in the future.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metal-temple.com/site/catalogues/entry/reviews/cd_3/b_2/british-lion-the.htm|title=Metal-Temple.com :: British Lion \u2013 The Burning (CD Review)|last=bkarr272|website=www.metal-temple.com|language=EN|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n[[Classic Rock (magazine)|Classic Rock]] rated the album a 4/5, and believes \"''The Burning'' sounds vastly more punchy and powerful than its predecessor, while also giving the distinct impression that British Lion have evolved into a fiery and characterful ensemble with a strong identity of their own\". The review continued by stating that \"we are still firmly in traditional rock territory here, and Harris's love of [[UFO (band)|UFO]] and [[Golden Earring]] remains as cheerfully conspicuous as ever, but thanks to a brighter, breezier sound and unmistakable hints of looseness and swagger, everything from the briskly uplifting title track to the brooding hulk of \"Bible Black\" sparkles with freshness and weirdly youthful vigour\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.loudersound.com/reviews/british-lion-arrys-other-army-return-on-sizzling-form|title=British Lion: \u2018Arry\u2019s other army return on sizzling form|last=January 2020|first=Dom Lawson 17|website=Classic Rock Magazine|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nCryptic Rock said British Lion are one of the more interesting and intriguing side projects in [[Hard rock]] and [[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]] today. Arguably the most dynamic and engaging bassist of his time, [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] is best known for emphatically standing on stage with his foot on the amp while pounding out ferocious bass riffs for [[Iron Maiden]]. Hearing these lions roar, let\u2019s step into the cage and feel ''The Burning''. As a first time listener of British Lion, one will immediately notice the distinct difference between British Lion and the melodic technical ecstasy of [[Iron Maiden]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://crypticrock.com/british-lion-the-burning-album-review/|title=British Lion - The Burning (Album Review)|last=Tanzi|first=Vito|date=2020-01-15|website=Cryptic Rock|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nKNAC stated that \"good things come to those who wait\". \"''The Burning'' is a molten magma of soaring and even syncopated vocals that hover over sometimes haunting neo-Celtic melodies and sometimes epic, wistful and melancholic lyrical themes\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.knac.com/article.asp?ArticleID=35238|title=KNAC.COM - Reviews - BRITISH LION 'The Burning'|website=www.knac.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs are written by Richard Taylor, David Hawkins and [[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]], except where noted.\n{{Track listing\n|headline = ''The Burning'' track listing\n| total_length    = 60:11\n| title1          = City of Fallen Angels\n| length1         = 5:20\n| writer1         = \n\n| title2          = The Burning\n| length2         = 5:15\n| writer2         = \n\n| title3          = Father Lucifer\n| length3         = 4:38\n| writer3         = \n\n| title4          = Elysium\n| length4         = 5:11\n| writer4         =\n\n| title5          = Lightning\n| length5         = 5:49\n| writer5         = \n\n| title6          = Last Chance\n| length6         = 6:05\n| writer6         = Grahame Leslie, Ian Roberts, Taylor, Harris\n\n| title7          = Legend\n| length7         = 4:06\n| writer7         = \n\n| title8          = Spit Fire\n| length8         = 6:19\n| writer8         = \n\n| title9          = Land of the Perfect People\n| length9         = 4:52\n| writer9         = Taylor, Harris\n\n| title10         = Bible Black \n| length10        = 6:33\n| writer10        = \n\n| title11         = Native Son\n| length11        = 6:03\n| writer11        = \n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*Richard Taylor \u2013 vocals\n*David Hawkins \u2013 guitars\n*Grahame Leslie \u2013 guitars\n*[[Steve Harris (musician)|Steve Harris]] \u2013 bass guitars, keyboards, production\n*Simon Dawson \u2013 drums\n\n===Additional personnel===\n*Tony Newton \u2013 engineering, recording, mixing\n*Ade Emsley \u2013 mastering\n*John McMurtrie \u2013 photography\n*Gustavo Sazes \u2013 album cover\n*Matt Cox \u2013 templating, booklet artwork\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of 2020 albums]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burning, The}}\n[[Category:Heavy metal albums by English artists]]\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Burning\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[British Lion (band)|British Lion]]\n| cover      = British Lion The Burning.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = January 17, 2020\n| recorded   = \n| venue      = \n| studio     = Barnyard Studio, Harlow, Essex, UK\n| genre      = [[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]] \n| length     = 60:11\n| label      = *[[Parlophone]] <small>(International edition)</small>\n*Explorer1 Music, LLC\n*[[Warner Music]] <small>(Japanese edit